   "source": [
    "# 📅 Day 032: Logistic Regression Implementation\n",
    "\n",
    "**Description:** Classifier fit/predict, probability scores, coefficient interpretation.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Subtopics to learn:**\n",
    "  - Logistic Regression workflow\n",
    "  - StandardScaler before LR (Importance of scaling)\n",
    "  - predict vs predict_proba (Thresholding and decisions)\n",
    "  - Coefficient interpretation (Odds ratios and feature influence)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📖 Concept Notes\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1. The Logistic Regression Workflow\n",
    "Logistic Regression modeling follows a sequence:\n",
    "1. **Linear Combination ($z$):** Calculate the raw log-odds score: $z = w^T x + b$\n",
    "2. **Activation ($\sigma$):** Map $z$ to a probability using the Sigmoid (Logistic) function: $p = \\frac{1}{1 + e^{-z}}$\n",
    "3. **Thresholding:** Apply a decision threshold (typically $0.5$) to classify as $1$ (if $p \\ge 0.5$) or $0$ (if $p < 0.5$).\n",
    "\n",
    "### 2. Importance of Feature Scaling (`StandardScaler`)\n",
    "- **Regularization Equivalence:** Scikit-learn's `LogisticRegression` applies L2 regularization by default. Regularization adds a penalty term proportional to the magnitude of the weights ($||w||_2^2$). If features are on different scales, features with larger ranges will have smaller weights, making them less penalized by regularization. Scaling ensures all features are regularized equally.\n",
    "- **Optimization Speed:** Gradient descent solvers (like `lbfgs` or `saga`) converge much faster when the loss surface is spherical (which occurs when features have similar variances) rather than elongated.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3. `predict` vs `predict_proba`\n",
    "- `predict_proba(X)`: Returns an $N \\times 2$ matrix containing the predicted probability for class 0 and class 1. These probabilities sum to 1 for each sample.\n",
    "- `predict(X)`: Returns the hard class label (0 or 1). It is equivalent to applying a $0.5$ threshold to the probability of class 1: `(predict_proba(X)[:, 1] >= 0.5).astype(int)`.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 4. Coefficient Interpretation (Odds Ratios)\n",
    "- **Log-Odds Change:** The weight $w_i$ tells us how the log-odds of the positive class changes with a 1-unit increase in feature $x_i$ (holding all other features constant).\n",
    "- **Odds Ratio ($e^{w_i}$):** Exp-transforming the weight yields the **Odds Ratio**. An odds ratio $> 1.0$ ($w_i > 0$) means the feature increases the probability of the positive class. An odds ratio $< 1.0$ ($w_i < 0$) means the feature decreases it."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from sklearn.datasets import load_breast_cancer\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, confusion_matrix, accuracy_score\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set design theme\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style=\"whitegrid\")\n",
    "plt.rcParams[\"figure.figsize\"] = (10, 6)\n",
    "plt.rcParams[\"font.size\"] = 12"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 💻 Code & Practice: Data Loading & Preprocessing"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load dataset\n",
    "data = load_breast_cancer()\n",
    "X = pd.DataFrame(data.data, columns=data.feature_names)\n",
    "y = pd.Series(data.target, name=\"target\") # 0 = malignant, 1 = benign\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f"Dataset shape: {X.shape}")\n",
    "print(f"Class distribution:\\n{y.value_counts(normalize=True)}")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Train/Test Split (stratified to maintain class balance)\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
    "    X, y, test_size=0.2, stratify=y, random_state=42\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f"Train size: {X_train.shape[0]}, Test size: {X_test.shape[0]}")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Scale features\n",
    "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train)\n",
    "X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "X_train_scaled_df = pd.DataFrame(X_train_scaled, columns=X.columns)\n",
    "print("\\nFeatures successfully scaled (Mean = 0, Std = 1).")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🛠️ Build / Submit Task: Model Training & Coefficient Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Fit Logistic Regression classifier\n",
    "model = LogisticRegression(random_state=42, max_iter=1000)\n",
    "model.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Coefficient Extraction\n",
    "coef_df = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    \"Feature\": X.columns,\n",
    "    \"Coefficient (Weight)\": model.coef_[0],\n",
    "    \"Odds Ratio\": np.exp(model.coef_[0])\n",
    "}).sort_values(by=\"Coefficient (Weight)\", key=abs, ascending=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "print("Top 10 Most Influential Features:")\n",
    "print(coef_df.head(10).to_string(index=False))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot Coefficients\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))\n",
    "top_coefs = coef_df.head(15)\n",
    "sns.barplot(\n",
    "    x=\"Coefficient (Weight)\",\n",
    "    y=\"Feature\",\n",
    "    data=top_coefs,\n",
    "    palette=\"coolwarm\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Top 15 Feature Coefficients (Malignant vs Benign)\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Coefficient (Weight)\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Feature Name\")\n",
    "plt.axvline(0, color=\"black\", linestyle=\"--\", linewidth=1)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(\"feature_coefficients.png\", dpi=150)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📈 Probability Distribution & Threshold Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Get predictions & probabilities\n",
    "y_pred = model.predict(X_test_scaled)\n",
    "y_prob = model.predict_proba(X_test_scaled)[:, 1] # Probability of being Benign (1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create comparison dataframe\n",
    "pred_comparison = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    \"Actual\": y_test,\n",
    "    \"Predicted Label\": y_pred,\n",
    "    \"Probability (Benign)\": y_prob\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "print("First 10 Predictions:")\n",
    "print(pred_comparison.head(10).to_string())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot Probability distributions\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))\n",
    "sns.histplot(\n",
    "    data=pred_comparison,\n",
    "    x=\"Probability (Benign)\",\n",
    "    hue=\"Actual\",\n",
    "    kde=True,\n",
    "    bins=20,\n",
    "    element=\"step\",\n",
    "    stat=\"density\",\n",
    "    common_norm=False\n",
    ")\n",
    "plt.axvline(0.5, color=\"red\", linestyle=\"--\", linewidth=2, label=\"Decision Boundary (0.5)\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Distribution of Predicted Probabilities by True Class\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Predicted Probability of Class 1 (Benign)\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Density\")\n",
    "plt.legend(labels=[\"Decision Boundary (0.5)\", \"Benign (1)\", \"Malignant (0)\"])\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(\"probability_distribution.png\", dpi=150)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## ✅ Verification & Evaluation Metrics"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Compute Evaluation Metrics\n",
    "accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)\n",
    "conf_matrix = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f"Test Accuracy: {accuracy:.4f}")\n",
    "print("\\nClassification Report:")\n",
    "print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred, target_names=data.target_names))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot Confusion Matrix Heatmap\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(6, 5))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(\n",
    "    conf_matrix,\n",
    "    annot=True,\n",
    "    fmt=\"d\",\n",
    "    cmap=\"Blues\",\n",
    "    xticklabels=data.target_names,\n",
    "    yticklabels=data.target_names\n",
    ")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Confusion Matrix\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Actual Label\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Predicted Label\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(\"confusion_matrix.png\", dpi=150)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Programmatic verification assertions\n",
    "assert accuracy > 0.95, f\"Accuracy was {accuracy:.4f}, expected > 0.95!\"\n",
    "assert X_train_scaled.shape[1] == 30, \"Feature count incorrect!\"\n",
    "print(\"All assertions passed successfully!\")"
   ]
  }
